comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: I'm not so familiar with ASIC.to firmware but I would like to ask if you are running t17 at immersion cooling? I just notice that it didn't detect fan speed under your screenshot it might be the cause of the problem why it keeps restarting.According to Asic.to this one below it will automatically restart in case of any failure.Code:7) Added a trigger for the maximum number of miner restarts in case of a board failure.So there might be other issue under your hashboard that cause miner auto restart.

comments.author: JustaVirus
comments.body: Quote from: BitMaxz on May 19, 2022, 10:29:23 PMI'm not so familiar with ASIC.to firmware but I would like to ask if you are running t17 at immersion cooling? I just notice that it didn't detect fan speed under your screenshot it might be the cause of the problem why it keeps restarting.According to Asic.to this one below it will automatically restart in case of any failure.Code:7) Added a trigger for the maximum number of miner restarts in case of a board failure.So there might be other issue under your hashboard that cause miner auto restart.Hello. Yes, I removed the fans and enabled immersion mode. I decided to turn off profile preset and manually set freq and voltage. It has been running smoothly for 12 hours now. hashing at 38T drawing 1.9kw.
